# Tokens

Tokens are how we keep Pathogen consistent: change `--pvc-color-accent-solid` once in CSS, and every button that uses it updates. Write components in terms of **roles** (`--pvc-color-accent-solid`), not palette stops (`primary-700`).

## Theme overrides for host apps

| Variable | Default | Host apps |
|----------|---------|-----------|
| `--color-primary-*` | Blue | Your brand / action colour (IRIDA: green) |
| `--color-neutral-*` | Slate (as `neutral-*`) | Leave as-is; use `neutral-*` in components |
| `--font-sans` | Inter stack | Optional swap |
| `--font-mono` | System mono | Code and IDs |

Use `neutral-*` in components, not raw `slate-*` — `neutral` is the public name; slate is an implementation detail in the theme file.

## Three layers

```
Palette (primary, neutral, status hues)
    ↓
Semantic roles (--pvc-color-*, --type-*, --pvc-radius-*, motion)
    ↓
Component-scoped (data grid, tooltip placement)
```

Grid and tooltip tokens are internal — don't override them from host apps unless you're theming the whole grid.

## Colour roles

Swatches show Pathogen defaults. Hosts remap accent through `--color-primary-*`.

