### When to use which accent token

| Situation | Tokens |
|-----------|--------|
| Text, borders, outline/ghost on a surface | `accent`, `accent-strong` |
| Filled primary button | `accent-solid`, `accent-solid-hover` |
| Outline/ghost destructive | `danger-strong`, `danger` |
| Filled destructive | `danger-solid`, `danger-solid-hover` |

In dark mode, **text and borders** on accent lighten for contrast; **solid button fills** stay saturated. Focus is special — it stays at `primary-500` in both modes so it never matches accent ([foundations → focus](<%= page_path :design-system-design-contract %>#focus-and-keyboard)).

## Type scale

```css
--type-meta: 0.75rem;      /* 12px */
--type-control: 0.875rem;  /* 14px */
--type-body: 1rem;         /* 16px */
--type-section: 1.25rem;   /* 20px */
--type-page: 2rem;         /* 32px — target; CSS may still say 31px until fixed */
```

| Token | px | Tailwind | Used by |
|-------|-----|----------|---------|
| `--type-meta` | 12 | `text-xs` | Hints, `CopyableValue` |
| `--type-control` | 14 | `text-sm` | Labels, buttons |
| `--type-body` | 16 | `text-base` | Body text |
| `--type-section` | 20 | `text-xl` | Section titles |
| `--type-page` | 32 | `text-3xl` | Page headings |

14px and 16px are the everyday sizes. The scale is **role-based**, not a strict mathematical ratio — each step is the smallest jump that still reads as a different level. Page size targets a clean **32px**; shipped CSS may still have 31px from an old rounding pass (on the fix list below).

## Spacing

4px base, Tailwind scale — not tokenised, just use it consistently:

| px | Class | Good for |
|----|-------|----------|
| 4 | `1` | Tight padding |
| 8 | `2` | Control internals |
| 12 | `3` | Radio rows |
| 16 | `4` | Form gaps |
| 24 | `6` | Sections |
| 32 | `8` | Major regions |

## Radius

```css
--pvc-radius-control-sm: 0.125rem; /* 2px */
--pvc-radius-control: 0.25rem;     /* 4px */
--pvc-radius-action: 0.375rem;     /* 6px */
--pvc-radius-panel: 0.5rem;        /* 8px */
```

Prefer `rounded-[var(--pvc-radius-action)]` over guessing `rounded-md` when you know the role.

## Elevation

```css
--pvc-shadow-none: none;
--pvc-shadow-overlay: 0 1px 3px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2);
```

Flat UI + borders; shadow only on floating layers. [Foundations → elevation](<%= page_path :design-system-design-contract %>#elevation) explains why we stopped at two shadow tokens.

## Motion

```css
--pvc-duration-fast: 120ms;
--pvc-duration-default: 160ms;
--pvc-duration-overlay: 200ms;
```

Colour and opacity first; movement for overlays. Honour `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Component-specific tokens

**Data grid** — `--pvc-data-grid-*` for borders, cell padding, body background. Internal to the grid.

**Tooltip** — `--pvc-tooltip-origin` for placement. Tooltip fill uses `neutral-950`; that's overlay territory, not page canvas.

## Where components are today

| Component | Semantic colour | Radius tokens | Type tokens |
|-----------|-----------------|---------------|-------------|
| `Button` | ✓ | `--pvc-radius-action` | via `text-sm` |
| `CopyableValue` | ✓ | `--pvc-radius-action` | `--type-meta` |
| `Typography` | partial | Tailwind | Tailwind |
| `Link`, `Tabs`, `Form` | partial | mixed | `text-sm` labels |
| `DataGrid` | grid-scoped | `rounded-lg` ≈ panel | — |
| `Tooltip` | hard-coded | `rounded-lg` | — |

New work: follow `Button`.

