## What's on our list

These docs describe where we're headed; CSS describes what's shipped. Four known gaps — close each in CSS and delete the row:

| # | Token | Shipped now | Target | Why |
|---|-------|-------------|--------|-----|
| 1 | `accent-solid-hover` | Lightens (`700` → `600`) | Darken (e.g. `800`) | Solid hover should press in, like danger already does |
| 2 | `focus` (dark) | `primary-400` (= accent) | `primary-500` both modes | Focus must stay separate from accent |
| 3 | `type-page` | 31px | 32px | Clean grid-aligned page title |
| 4 | `success` / `warning` ladders | Base only | Full solid/outline set like accent | Solid success/warning buttons aren't supported yet |

Until row 4 lands, don't build solid success/warning surfaces with hand-rolled `emerald-*` / `amber-*`.
